title: Live coverage: SpaceX to launch 100th Direct to Cell Starlink satellite on Falcon 9 flight from Cape Canaveral
summary: The overnight mission will also see the return of Falcon 9 booster, tail number B1073, which experienced an abort as its engine began firing during the June 14 launch attempt of the Starlink 10-2 mission. Liftoff from pad 40 at Cape Canaveral Space Force Station is set for 2:57 a.m. EDT (0657 UTC).

title: Launch Roundup: Falcon Heavy returns with GOES-U, Firefly Alpha launch attempt
summary: Following a week in which Tropical Storm Alberto brought high seas, wind, and rain-related delays to the launch schedule in Florida, SpaceX managed to get back on track this week with launches from all three of the active Falcon launch pads, including a Falcon Heavy.
